title.narrative: 4.4 BIRTH REGISTRATION

description.narrative: 4.4 Government has strengthened capacity to scale up the birth registration of children within a harmonized CRVS system, which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, fewer children experience physical and sexual violence, abuse and exploitation

title.narrative: 4.4 Government has strengthened capacity to scale up the birth registration of children within a harmonized CRVS system

description.narrative: In 2021, an additional 21,500 (cumulative 25,000) people had improved knowledge and practices on birth registration services, more than the set target (10,750) for year. UNICEF supported the capacity of National Civil Registration Authority (NCRA) to scale up birth registration within a harmonized civil registration and vital statistics (CRVS) system and an additional 1,250 civil registrars and other cadre were trained on the use of a digital mobile application for birth and death notification and registration, bringing the cumulative total to 2,703 against a country programme target of 5,000 by 2023; signifying that this output is on track.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
